            %a{"data-role" => "button", "data-transition" => "fade", :href => "/mobile/docs/forms/switch/methods"} Methods
          %li
            %a.ui-btn-active{"data-role" => "button", "data-transition" => "fade", :href => "/mobile/docs/forms/switch/events"} Events
        %p
          Bind events directly to the
          %code select
          element.  Use jQuery Mobile's
          = succeed "," do
            %a{:href => "/mobile/docs/api/events"} virtual events
          or bind standard JavaScript events, like change, focus, blur, etc.:
        %pre
          %code
            :preserve
              $( ".selector" ).bind( "change", function(event, ui) {
                ...
              });
        %p The slider plugin has the following custom event:
        %dl
          %dt
            %code create
            triggered when a slider is created
          %dd
            %pre
              %code
                :preserve
                  $( ".selector" ).slider({
                     create: function(event, ui) { ... }
                  });
    / /content-primary
